often a </a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" b="1" dirty="0"><a:solidFill><a:srgbClr val="0E9ED5"/></a:solidFill></a:rPr><a:t>good idea to prepare some annex slides</a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" b="1" dirty="0"/><a:t> </a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t>(included at the end of the deck) to provide clear, succinct, and visual explanations of key technical concepts that you talk about in your main deck.</a:t></a:r></a:p><a:p><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t>Best part: </a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" b="1" dirty="0"/><a:t>you can reuse them for other projects</a:t></a:r><a:r><a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/><a:t>!</a:t></a:r></a:p></p:txBody></p:sp></p:spTree><p:extLst><p:ext uri="{BB962C8B-B14F-4D97-AF65-F5344CB8AC3E}"><p14:creationId xmlns:p14="http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/powerpoint/2010/main" val="2117427900"/></p:ext></p:extLst></p:cSld><p:clrMapOvr><a:masterClrMapping/></p:clrMapOvr></p:sld>